Interface ObservationTableReader<I,D>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - input symbol class
    D - observation (output) domain class
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface ObservationTableReader<I,D>
    Reads an ObservationTable from a string source.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ObservationTable<I,D> read(String source, Alphabet<I> alphabet)
      Reads the string representation of an observation table and returns an implementation of ObservationTable which allows access to short and long prefixes as well as suffixes.

    • Method Detail

      • read

        ObservationTable<I,D> read(String source,
                           Alphabet<I> alphabet)
        Reads the string representation of an observation table and returns an implementation of ObservationTable which allows access to short and long prefixes as well as suffixes.
        Parameters:
        source - The string representation to read, must not be null.
        alphabet - The learning alphabet containing the symbols used, must not be null.
        Returns:
        an implementation of ObservationTable which allows at lease access to ObservationTable.getSuffixes(), ObservationTable.getShortPrefixes(), and ObservationTable.getLongPrefixes(). Will never be null.
